# Numbers Chapter 7 — The SOPHIA Bible (Consensus)
**Arbiter:** SOPHIA | **In council with:** EMET, LOGOS, PNEUMA
**Source Manuscript:** Leningrad Codex (B19A), pp. 154–157; Codex Vaticanus (Vat.gr.1209), pa_0116–0118 (LXX) | **Source Images:** `source-texts/hebrew-OT/NUM_007_page_001.jpg` through `NUM_007_page_004.jpg`; `source-texts/greek-OT-LXX/NUM_007_vaticanus_page_001.jpg` through `NUM_007_vaticanus_page_003.jpg`

---

## The Wagons and Oxen of the Leaders (vv. 1–9)

**7:1** And it came to pass on the day that Moses finished setting up the tabernacle, that he anointed it and consecrated it and all its vessels, and the altar and all its vessels; and he anointed them and consecrated them.

**7:2** And the leaders of Israel, the heads of the houses of their fathers, brought an offering. They were the leaders of the tribes; they were the ones who stood over those who were numbered.

**7:3** And they brought their offering before YHWH: six covered wagons and twelve oxen -- a wagon for every two of the leaders and an ox for each one -- and they brought them before the tabernacle.

**7:4** And YHWH spoke to Moses, saying:

**7:5** "Take it from them, and they shall be for performing the service of the Tent of Meeting. And you shall give them to the Levites, each man according to his service."

**7:6** And Moses took the wagons and the oxen and gave them to the Levites.

**7:7** Two wagons and four oxen he gave to the sons of Gershon, according to their service.

**7:8** And four wagons and eight oxen he gave to the sons of Merari, according to their service, under the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.

**7:9** But to the sons of Kohath he gave none, for the service of the holy things belonged to them; upon the shoulder they carried them.

---

## The Dedication of the Altar (vv. 10–11)

**7:10** And the leaders brought the dedication offering of the altar on the day it was anointed; and the leaders brought their offering before the altar.

**7:11** And YHWH said to Moses: "One leader each day, one leader each day, they shall bring their offering for the dedication of the altar."

---

## Day One: Nahshon of Judah (vv. 12–17)

**7:12** And the one who brought his offering on the first day was Nahshon the son of Amminadab, of the tribe of Judah.

**7:13** And his offering was one silver dish, its weight one hundred and thirty shekels; one silver basin of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering;

**7:14** one golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense;

**7:15** one young bull, one ram, one male lamb in its first year, for a burnt offering;

**7:16** one male goat for a sin offering;

**7:17** and for the sacrifice of the peace offerings: two oxen, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs in their first year. This was the offering of Nahshon the son of Amminadab.

